<br>
Al-Qaeda isn't crippled, the IISS report shows that they are strengthened both numerically and in terms of popular support.  Iraq's proved to be the best recruiting seargent for jihadis since the Suez crisis.  The report also says that the nations fighting terrorism have had their power diluted by &quot;belligerent unilateralism&quot;- whereas the unity between Al-Qaeda affiliated groups has been strengthened by the Iraq war.  <br>
